JOHANNESBURG - There's been a dramatic increase in our daily COVID-19 death toll with 457 more people passing away in South Africa after contracting the virus. These latest fatalities - recorded over the past 24 hours - take the national tally to 62,628. For a third consecutive day, the daily caseload has remained under the 20,000 mark, with 15,501 tests coming back positive over the past day. On the vaccine front, 3 631 102 jabs have been administered so far. As of today the cumulative number of #COVID19 cases identified in SA is 2 090 909 with 15 501 new cases reported. Today 457 deaths have been reported which brings the total to  62 628 deaths. The cumulative recoveries now stand at 1 845 038 representing  a recovery rate of 88.2% pic.twitter.com/JXzxLYUXZl  Download the Eyewitness News app to your iOS  or Android  device.